# Security Tracker Python

## Overview

Security Tracker Python is a beginner-friendly cybersecurity project that monitors user login activity and identifies suspicious behaviour based on failed login attempts and administrator access.

The script generates a security report and alerts security teams when abnormal activity is detected.

This project demonstrates core SOC (Security Operations Centre) concepts using Python.

---

## Features

- User login monitoring
- Failed login tracking
- Admin access verification
- Suspicious activity detection
- Security report generation
- Multiple IP address monitoring

---

## Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Ubuntu Linux
- Virtual Environment (venv)
- Nano Text Editor

---

## Source Code Summary

The script:

1. Accepts user login information
2. Tracks failed login attempts
3. Displays monitored IP addresses
4. Checks administrative access
5. Generates security alerts when suspicious behaviour is detected

---

## How It Works

### Inputs

- Username
- Failed Login Attempts

### Security Checks

| Check | Condition |
|---------|-----------|
| Suspicious Activity Alert | Failed logins > 5 |
| Admin Access Monitoring | Admin status enabled |
| IP Monitoring | Displays monitored IP list |

